    "Other example includes the Smart-Cane and Smart-Walker, which can detect obstacles and build a map of their surroundings in order to localize the user inside the map, and subsequently guide them to different waypoints [88].In some cases, both mobility and manipulation support are needed.",
    "Wheelchair-mounted robot arms can provide improved means of manipulating objects.",
    "Examples include PerMMA [89,90] and JACO [91].",
    "In these systems, the user's motion intention is commonly extracted through either manual manipulation (e.g., joysticks and buttons) or sensors implanted in the user's body [92].Another technology that provides both mobility and manipulation support is wearable robots such as prostheses, orthoses, and exoskeletons [9,[93][94][95].",
    "A prosthesis is a device that supplants a person's missing limb."
